15 Art. 658.1. Motion for intervention
16 A. At any stage of a proceeding, upon written motion to intervene and after
17 a contradictory hearing, the court may allow a relative or other suitable individual
18 to intervene on behalf of himself or a party if good cause is shown that intervention
19 is in the best interest of the child and, after adjudication, will facilitate permanency
20 for the child. The court may deny the motion to intervene or set a contradictory
21 hearing with notice to all parties.
