25 present evidence at an adjudication hearing except when called as a witness by a
26 party. An intervenor shall not inspect or copy any record of the case before an in
27 camera inspection by the court and an opportunity to be heard by the parties.
28 C. The court may exclude an intervenor from any part of a hearing as
29 necessary to protect the privacy interests of the parent or child.
